<section id="hotels">
  <title>Hotels</title>

  <p>We have a room block with the
  <link href="http://www.millenniumhotels.com/usa/millenniumcincinnati/">Millennium
  Hotel Cincinnati</link>. The Millennium is in the heart of downtown and is a short
  walk from our venue and all social events. We have single, double, triple, and quad
  occupancy rooms available, each for $109 per night.</p>

  <p><link href="https://reservations.millenniumhotels.com/ibe/details.aspx?propertyid=13546&amp;nights=1&amp;checkin=09/25/2015&amp;group=1509OPENHE">Use this link to book online with our room block.</link>
  Or, call +1-800-876-2100 and reference "Open Help Conference".</p>

  <p>The Millennium Hotel Cincinnati has a rooftop outdoor swimming pool. The pool
  may still be open in late September, depending on weather.</p>
</section>

<section id="transportation">
  <title>Transportation</title>

  <p>Cincinnati is served by the
  <link href="http://www.cvgairport.com/">Cincinnati/Northern Kentucky
  International Airport (CVG)</link>. Shuttles between the airport and downtown are
  available from
  <link href="http://executivetransportation.org/">Executive Transportation</link>
  at $32 round-trip.</p>

  <p>Use the
  <link href="http://www.go-metro.com/">Cincinnati Metro bus</link> to visit other
  parts of Cincinnati, or the
  <link href="http://www.tankbus.org/">TANK bus</link> to visit Northern Kentucky.</p>
</section>

